bsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br><span class=title>   A few additional words about myself...</span><hr size=1> Howdy all,<br>
<br>
I just wanted to explain why I had to leave the Hole raid after we finished up CR but before the raid was over.  I have a chronic illness called Fibromyalgia and part of controlling my illness includes keeping a rigid schedule of when I go to sleep at night and when I get up in the morning. In my case I always log off of EQ at night by 11:00 EST at the latest.  <br>
<br>
I had a great time on the raid the other night and would love to do other night raids with Avvisione provided that my leaving by 11:00 doesn't cause any problems.  Even if there are certain raids where I can't go because my leaving by 11:00 would disrupt the raid I can still be available before the raid starts to do taxi service to the meeting location.<br>
<br>
The below link is to a web site that has good information on the illness.  <br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.fmnetnews.com/pages/basics.html">www.fmnetnews.com/pages/basics.html</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <br>
<br>
Please feel free to contact me in game if you have any questions on Fibromyalgia that the web site did not answer<br>
<br>
Thank you,<br>
Loralin Taborwin <br>
54th lvl druid<br>
